@node Introduktion "What's this VideoDB for?"


                            INTRODUCTION


VideoDB is a database for David Ekholm's db2.10+. The reason why I did 
this project, was simply that I needed one for my videocollection :)
I choosed db for this as I find db small, simple and fast. The arexx-
port is also very good. 


Why make VideoDB public??? I can make a database like VideoDB, without 
much effort.. 

- At first VideoDB seems like any other project done in db, but there's
  one big difference: I wrote an arexx script that calculates how
  much time there is left on the Videotape. Now when you see a movie
  in your newspaper, you only need to start VideoDB, and see which 
  tape that has time left for the movie, and get it from your pile
  of tapes :)

It took some time for me writing the arexx-script as it's the first
time I make something in arexx! If you find anything that can make
the script more effective, please don't just change your own script!
Send me an e-mail and tell me, so that I can make the changes to
a new version.


@endnode

@node Krav "Vad du behöver"


                             Requirements


För att kunna använda VideoDB behöver du:

* an amiga :)
* AmigaOS 2.04+ (to be able to run db)
* Arexx must be active with RexxMast (Sys:System/)
* db2.10 or higher (is availible on Aminet under biz/dbase,
                    the current version is at this time 3.2).



@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"


                            INSTALLATION


I did'nt make any Installer-script as the Installer program would take
too much space in the archive. 

The installation is very easy if you've used your amiga a couple of
weeks :) 
 
In Workbench, just drag the drawer into the drawer where you have db.
Then delete the VideoDB.swe-drawer.
Swedish users: Dra VideoDB.Swe-lĺdan över fönstret där du har db,
och döp om lĺdan till VideoDB.

In Shell, go to the location where the VideoDB-drawer is and type:

copy videodb <location of db> all
Ex. copy videodb work:dbase/db all

Then go to the location where VideoDB now is and type:

delete VideoDB.swe all 

Swedish users: Gĺ till stället där du har VideoDB-lĺdan och gĺ in i den.

Skriv: copy videodb.swe <platsen där du har db>/VideoDB all
Ex. copy videodb.sve work:dbase/db/VideoDB all


@endnode

@node Användning "Hur man använder VideoDB"


                               USAGE


Double-click on VideoDB's Icon, or load it from db.
Now you can start typing in the fields. 

Title        = The name of the film...                  (Terminator II)
Category     = Category...                              (Action)
Time         = Lenght on the movie in hours and minutes (1.57) 
Year         = Year when the movie was made or whatever (1992)
Actors       = The actors in the movie...               (Arnold Sczxczegger)
Tape         = The number on the Videotape              (15)
Length       = Length on the tape in minutes            (240)
Left         = Time left on the tape (written automatic)(2.03)
Lended to    = Is the tape with anyone else???        (Mr. Incognito 960807)

In the Arexx menu you can search for actionmovies, comedies and so on.
Then DB searches for ex. action in the field 'Category'. The first film
that is an actionmovie shows up. When you press enter, the next one 
shows up. If you wrote 'ActionComedy' in one film, it will show up both
when you search for Action, and for Comedy. You can add your own search-
categories, read more about this in the db.guide under 'arexxmenus'.



@endnode

